  "name": {
    "en": "Ginsenosides",
    "zh-Hant": "人蔘皂苷",
    "zh-Hans": "人参皂苷"
  },
  "chebiID": "CHEBI:73682",
  "description": {
    "en": "A group of triterpene saponins (ginsenosides) that are the major bioactive compounds in ginseng. Over 30 different ginsenosides have been identified, classified into dammarane-type structures. They are divided into protopanaxadiol (PPD) and protopanaxatriol (PPT) groups based on their aglycone structure.",
    "zh-Hant": "人蔘中的主要生物活性成分群，為三萜皂苷（人蔘皂苷）。已鑑定出30多種，分類為達瑪烷型結構。根據苷元結構分為原人蔘二醇（PPD）和原人蔘三醇（PPT）兩組。"
  },
  "molecularFormula": "C54H92O24 (Rb1 example)",
  "molecularWeight": 1109.29,
  "compoundClass": "Triterpene saponin; Dammarane-type",
  "foundIn": [
